'''Level 760''' is the '''761<sup>st</sup>''' level of '''[[The Backrooms]]''' and is between '''[[Level 759]]''' and '''[[Level 761]]'''.
<div style="background-color:#000000; font-family:Open Sans; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
<center><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:30px">--【 '''Description''' 】--</span></center></div>
{{Blurimage Border|text-color=white|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=bhksadvgvhd|file=220-1.png|𝚏𝚒𝚐=1.0|caption=Photo of the outside of '''Level 760''', taken from the hostel side.|hovertext=Photo of the outside of '''Level 760''', taken from the hostel side.}}
'''Level 760''' resembles a functioning hostel at an unknown Russian boarding school, with one half a hostel and the other a school.

'''Level 760''' includes roughly 167 stories, all connected by stairways, and each floor has 70-90 rooms. Hallways have 2 blocks at the start and the end of the hallway; every block has 8 rooms. There are doors on the sides of the hallway; every room is numbered, with the hundred being the floor number and the final two digits being the room number. For example: 3 rooms on the 4<sup>th</sup> floor will be 403, 19 rooms on the 15<sup>th</sup> floor will be 1519.

'''Level 760''' contains windows in stairways and rooms. They will go to a random window in another location, but the view from the windows will display the outside and the other half of the hostel, which is the school half. On the 1<sup>st</sup> floor near the lobby is a nice fountain.

These water sources during the day will supply [[Object 1|Almond Water]], but during the night they will give [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]], and the liquid from the fountain will not change if collected in a bottle or container.

The rooms of '''Level 760''' all have unique themes on the classroom side, every room teaching a different subject or topic, while the hostel side provides simple, personal quarters. There is a strict schedule that one is given that and must keep before entering '''Level 760''', wanderers are given their own room on any floor. It is reported that there are very few students who seem to genuinely be in the school or attending classes. The students range from ages 14 to 19.

When it is day, 7:00 AM or later, it is possible to explore anywhere inside the school besides staff-restricted areas, hang out with people in one of the student rooms, attend classes, etc. At 10:00 PM, one must remain in their personal room, and at no point should leave it, as the night period has begun, and this is when any entities are located besides the unique entities populating '''Level 760'''.

<div style="background-color:#000000; font-family:Open Sans; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
<center><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:30px">--【 '''Personal Rooms''' 】--</span></center></div>
{{Blurimage Border|text-color=white|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=bhksadvgvhd|file=220-2.png|𝚏𝚒𝚐=2.0|caption=Photo of the inside of a personal room in '''Level 760'''.|hovertext=Photo of the inside of a personal room in '''Level 760'''.}}
When wanderers enter '''Level 760''', they are given their own personal room on any floor of the hostel side, and it's described as being furnished and comfortable by the those who have been in '''Level 760'''. One is allowed a personal computer and phone, and nothing is restricted as long as it follows appropriate school standards.

Things that are restricted are social media websites like '''YouTube, Reddit, Discord, Facebook, Instagram, etc.''' Miscellaneous websites and game websites like '''Cool Math Games, neal.fun, Roblox, etc.'''

There are occasional room checks, but nothing too common to the point one feels uncomfortable; it is just to make sure no weapons are smuggled in, despite no one ever leaving the school.

