<div style="background-color:#000000; font-family:Open Sans; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
<center><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:30px">--【 '''Entities''' 】--</span></center></div>
'''Level 760''' is devoid of hostile entities during the day period, but during the night period, there are reports of [[Entity 3|Smilers]] and [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]] appearing when a person is on a floor with no staff.
<div style="background-color:#000000; font-family:Open Sans; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
<center><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:30px">--【 '''Exclusive Entities of Level 760''' 】--</span></center></div>
<center><span style="font-size:20px;">'''The Hostel & School Staff'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
Like every school or hostel, there are staff, and many of them are teachers or security, and there are notes of a possible principal and other important individuals in the school, but there is no actual evidence recorded of encounters with them. The staff in the hostel are mainly individuals who serve to help with everyday accommodations and such.

The staff is always polite and respectful during the day, helping people get to classes and giving directions as well. When the night period begins, they do not drop the act of being respectful, and when they notice a wanderer outside of their personal room, they only ask to go back to the room, and will '''have to use force only if necessary.''' No one has reported being truly hurt by any staff.

It is speculated that they aren't entities but real people who came before any new wanderers and took over the school, running it as their own half hostel, half school, though most of the staff usually don't speak, and when they do, they speak Russian and not English, making communication quite difficult.
<center><span style="font-size:20px;">'''Bubblegum (Бабл гам)'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
''Бабл гам', or Bubblegum in English,''' is a year 10 - 11 student at the school and is not hostile. If he is in the vicinity of a wanderer who shouts, '''"Бабл гам,"''' out loud, he will get hostile and approach the wanderer either on the stairs or in the corridor. If you are on the stairs when he confronts one, he will toss an empty water bottle at them and walk away, seemingly forgetting about you.

He will be passive when confronting again, and in the corridor, he will twist one's ear jokingly, trying to annoy them. If one ignores him, then he'll walk away and become passive.
<center><span style="font-size:16px;">'''Anger Prone Incidents With Бабл гам'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
If one yells or tries to attack '''Бабл гам''', he will automatically assume the wanderer wants to fight and starts trying to hit them aggressively, there is no reward for besting him in a fist fight, but he will stop if one just runs away, not bothering to follow, though he will call the wanderer a sissy forever and tease them every time he sees if the wanderer did flee from him.
<div style="background-color:#000000; font-family:Open Sans; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
<center><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:30px">--【 '''Colonies & Outposts''' 】--</span></center></div>
There are no colonies or outposts, as there has been no need to establish a base of operations in '''Level 760''', but there are clubs for most topics taught in '''Level 760''', which are too many to list, and 95% of clubs are not very well-known due to the language barrier.
<div style="background-color:#000000; font-family:Open Sans; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
<center><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:30px">--【 '''Entrances & Exits''' 】--</span></center></div>
<center><span style="font-size:20px;">'''Entrances'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
*Going in the direction of entities on '''[[Level !]]''' has a 35% chance of bringing one here.
*No-clipping into a pipe on '''[[Level 2]]''' will have a 1% chance to lead one here.
*No-clipping into a lamp on '''[[Level 82]]''' has 20% chance of transporting one here.
*Jumping 3 or more times in the elevator on '''[[Level 922]]''' will cause the floor to break, and the wanderer will fall on the ground in '''[[Level 760]]'''.
*Surviving 3 days on '''[[Level 729]]''' leads here.
*A school campus found in the snowy depths of '''[[Level 759]]''' will send one here.
*Ditto with the '''[[Level 759]]''' exit, but this can also happen in '''[[Level 96]]''', even though '''[[Level 96]]''' is '''not''' snowy.
<center><span style="font-size:20px;">'''Exits'''</span></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
*Exiting from the main door in the lobby will transport to '''[[Level 11]]'''.
*Jumping out from any window will have a 10% chance to lead to '''[[Level 4]]'''.
*A hole in a wall in a clinic will lead to '''[[Level 297]]'''.
*Being caught by hostel staff will cause transportation to '''[[Level 80]]''' or '''[[Level 90]]'''.
*If '''бабл гам''' catches a wanderer, there is a 0.7% chance that instead of twisting their ear, he will drag you into '''[[Level 699]]'''.
